cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CY 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to identify the rhetorical roles of sentences in legal judgments. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses deep neural models, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with information retrieval and legal search, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with legal documents, which could place it in cs.CY (Computers and Society).
